  "prompt": "What are some lesser-known sights to see when visiting Aurora, IL?",
  "response": "Aurora, Illinois, has several lesser-known sights and attractions that can provide a unique experience for visitors. Here are some recommendations:\n\n1. **Phillips Park**: While many people are aware of the larger parks, Phillips Park is a hidden gem featuring beautiful gardens, a small zoo, and a scenic pond. The park offers walking trails, and the historic Phillips Park Family Aquatic Center is a great spot in warmer months.\n\n2. **Aurora Regional Fire Museum**: This museum showcases the history of firefighting in the Aurora area. With fascinating exhibits and vintage fire equipment, it's a great spot for history buffs and families.\n\n3. **The Art and History Center**: Located in the historic downtown area, this center often features rotating exhibits that showcase local art and history. It's a great place to learn more about Aurora's past and present.\n\n4. **Waubonsie Lake**: This is a peaceful spot to enjoy nature, take a walk, or have a picnic. It's a less crowded alternative to some of the larger parks in the area.\n\n5. **Leland Tower**: This distinctive building is one of Aurora's iconic structures. While you can't go up to the top, viewing it from below and learning about its history can be enjoyable for architecture enthusiasts.\n\n6. **Aurora Downtown**: Explore the hidden gems, including unique local shops, boutiques, and art installations. The area often features picturesque architecture and can be a lovely place to stroll.\n\n7. **Santori Public Library**: Beyond just a place to borrow books, this library hosts events and workshops and has a lovely architecture that\u2019s worth checking out, especially if you're an avid reader or enjoy quiet spaces.\n\n8. **McCarty Park**: This park features a little-known walking trail and various sports facilities. It's a pleasant spot for a quieter day out amidst the hustle and bustle of the city.\n\n9. **Pioneer Park**: This lesser-known park is great for outdoor activities, including sports fields and a beautiful playground that\u2019s ideal for families looking to enjoy some time outside.\n\n10. **The Paramount Theatre**: While it\u2019s more known than other entries on this list, it\u2019s worth attending a show or just admiring the beautifully restored building, which has hosted many notable performances and events.\n\nBy exploring these lesser-known sights, you'll get a more diverse and rich experience of Aurora beyond its more famous attractions.",
